Git Rebase:

# 

<span key="fc60713fb88c4cdcbe59078fd18b9aaa"><span offset-key="fc60713fb88c4cdcbe59078fd18b9aaa:0">Git Rebase</span></span>

## 

<span key="27ee2ff6532844a6a169985347b3c240"><span offset-key="27ee2ff6532844a6a169985347b3c240:0">Rebasing a feature branch from main</span></span>

<span key="9bf30ac57b074799821b79be9afbd09c"><span offset-key="9bf30ac57b074799821b79be9afbd09c:0">On occassion you'll find that you've been working on a feature branch and you need to merge in changes from master. This could just be a final step before you push a series of commits to github before creating a PR.</span></span>

<span key="226859e118cb461ab25010920d8d4b4b"><span offset-key="226859e118cb461ab25010920d8d4b4b:0">These steps are similar to what the "Rebase and Merge" action does on github.</span></span>

### 

<span key="a7b15f1144b34658a9e7aba89834570e"><span offset-key="a7b15f1144b34658a9e7aba89834570e:0">Objective</span></span>

<span key="00457d558e6a43feb752d2c7209bd19c"><span offset-key="00457d558e6a43feb752d2c7209bd19c:0">This guide will show you how to rebase (rebuild) a feature branch to begin at the current HEAD of the master branch. Think of it as if you are starting a new branch based on the current master and pasting all of your commits to the new branch.</span></span>

![](data:image/svg+xml;base64,)

<span key="a56433d4e6f144868de21d0643732ce4"><span offset-key="a56433d4e6f144868de21d0643732ce4:0">Never rebase a branch that has already been pushed to a remote (public, eg. the main branch) repository, such as github; doing so will cause conflicts and confusion among your team.</span></span>

### 

<span key="742d30c8ad604cf4a204c300df323b8c"><span offset-key="742d30c8ad604cf4a204c300df323b8c:0">Getting Started</span></span>

1.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">1.</span>
    <span key="ed3b13d1e17840eeb2fb2637c09a9a50"><span offset-key="ed3b13d1e17840eeb2fb2637c09a9a50:0">Make sure all changes are committed to your feature branch</span></span>

2.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">2.</span>
    <span key="96805dbaba67456f8f3559d899055c76"><span offset-key="96805dbaba67456f8f3559d899055c76:0">You will need to update your local master branch</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="a96c838075f142478da23d6f6a92dcfd">`> git checkout master`</span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="f9a853b247c848508e128eb3cee03e07">`> git pull origin master`</span>

3.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">3.</span>
    <span key="3420651708cd4f7883fd5c9835101260"><span offset-key="3420651708cd4f7883fd5c9835101260:0">Go back to your feature branch</span></span>

    -   <img src="data:image/svg+xml;base64," class="r-1nf4jbm" />

        <span key="2a05b2f275e84681aab77b58078677f6">`> git checkout feature-branch`</span>

4.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">4.</span>
    <span key="c9f7f78ac2c1460688864cd5d3c34d68"><span offset-key="c9f7f78ac2c1460688864cd5d3c34d68:0">Now we can rebase the feature branch onto </span>`master`</span>

    > <span key="fbbb598fdcf644c78ecd9ac266cf9692"><span offset-key="fbbb598fdcf644c78ecd9ac266cf9692:0">git rebase master First, rewinding head to replay your work on top of it... Applying: added staged command</span></span>

5.  <span class="r-1awozwy r-1nf4jbm r-6koalj r-18u37iz r-gg6oyi r-ubezar r-16dba41 r-135wba7 r-1m04atk r-1pyaxff" contenteditable="false" style="height:24px">5.</span>
    <span key="913065b641774a0fad381cdc14ba2c85"><span offset-key="913065b641774a0fad381cdc14ba2c85:0">Your commits will now show in the git log after the commits merged from master</span></span>
